<HEADLINE> UN to Hold Annual International School Student Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Annual U.N. International
School Student Conference is scheduled to be held at the
headquarters from March 4-5, 1999, United Nations Department of
Public Information said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Facing the New Millennium: a Search for Global Ethics" will be
the theme of the twenty-third session.
</P>
<P>
The annual conference is aimed to provide a forum for young
people to discuss global issues and to hear high profile experts'
views on the topic.
</P>
<P>
The two days of general debate and discussions will focus on
the impending millennium and the issues that the future
generations will face in hope of gaining an understanding of how
the youth of today will proceed into the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
Issues relating to controversial subjects such as human
rights, the media, the environment, the role of women in the
military, social affairs and the economy will also be examed and
discussed.  
