<HEADLINE> Environment Friendly Manufacturers Urged in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He was addressing participants at the on-going three-day
seminar on environmental management by manufacturers, organized
by the Conference of Environment Management of Zimbabwe in
Victoria Falls in west Zimbabwe, the Zimbabwe News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
He said environmental issues were now a fact of conducting
business and were shaping policies in governments worldwide as it
becomes imperative to use natural resources sustainable.
</P>
<P>
International standards reduced trade barriers and those
standards were practical tools to help developing countries manage
the impact of their activities on the environment, he said.
</P>
