<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Killed After UNITA Shells N. Angolan City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and another
four injured Wednesday after troops of the National Union for
Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) shelled Malanje City in
northern Angola.
</P>
<P>
Houses at the provincial broadcasting station and a hospital
were hit by the shellings, which resulted in the most serious
casualties in 10 days, the official news agency Angog reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of people have been killed or injured when UNITA
intensified its military actions around Malanje with long-range
artillery since the government forces recaptured Mbanza Congo,
capital city of Zaire Province on February 12.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the aim of UNITA's intensifying actions on
Malanje is to try to link up its forces in the north to those in
the central part of the country, where UNITA's headquarters in
Andulo and Bialundo are surrounded by the government forces.
</P>
<P>
UNITA men destroyed an important bridge Saturday 60 kms south
of Malanje, in order to prevent the advance of the government
forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
