<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce To Play Key Role In Aerospace Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Rolls-Royce Plc is involved in six
of eight Defense and Aerospace Research Partnerships (DARP)
launched Wednesday by the Government's Foresight Defense and
Aerospace Panel.
</P>
<P>
The company will also generate closer collaboration between
existing Rolls-Royce university technology centers (UTCs),
involving the universities of Birmingham, Swansea, Cambridge and
Oxford.
</P>
<P>
During a speech at the launch, Mike Goulette of Rolls-Royce,
said the UTC network has played an important role in forging the
strong links between industry and the academic community.
</P>
<P>
The collaboration is set to become even more precisely targeted
and managed through the formation of DARPs, he added.
</P>
<P>
The eight DARPs will research topics as varied as turbulence
modelling and advanced materials, and will each involve a
partnership of companies and universities.
</P>
<P>
The design DARP is based on the Rolls-Royce/British Aerospace
university technology partnership announced at last year's
Farnborough Air Show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
