<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-03 19:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese President Praises Young People for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese President Emile Lahoud on
Wednesday praised the country's youngsters for their brave actions
against the Israeli aggression on the country, the official
National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"Lebanon will never die as long as there are such young people
like those who participated in the campaign to liberate the
village Arnoun from Israeli occupation," Lahoud said when meeting
with representatives of those youngsters.
</P>
<P>
The young people achieved by their bare hands what the
diplomatics failed to do, Lahoud said, apparently referring to
the return of Arnoun on Saturday which was annexed by Israeli
forces into its so-called security zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The village, three kilometers from northern Israel, was
cordoned off with barbed wire and earth moulds by Israeli forces
and its allies South Lebanon Army on February 17.
</P>
<P>
Israel claimed that guerrillas of the Iranian-backed Hezbollah,
or Party of God, always used the village as a launching pad for
attacks against a nearby Israeli outpost at the crusader-era
Beaufort Castle.
</P>
<P>
Last week, hundreds of university students flocked to Arnoun
and removed all fencing around the village despite that Israeli
soldiers fired warning shoots into the air.
</P>
<P>
The students' move came when the Lebanese government's
diplomatic efforts appeared to be rapidly losing momentum.
</P>
<P>
Lahoud said he would always stand by the young people and
support their cause which is the cornerstone for Lebanon's
liberation process and democratic reform.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
