<DOCNO> XIE19990304.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8.9 Million Russians Unemployed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of unemployed in Russia
has soared to 8.9 million, or 12.4 percent of the work force, the
Labor Ministry said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of them, 1.1 million were made redundant in the aftermath of
the financial crisis that hit the country last August, when the
government devalued the ruble.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the jobless rate is likely to further rise to
12.7 percent by the end of the year, Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
The employment offices around the country had 1.9 million, or
2.7 percent of the economically active population, on register at
the end of last year. Women accounted for 64.6 percent of
registered unemployed.
</P>
<P>
The average job-seeker will need seven to eight months to get
reemployed.
</P>
<P>
There are six applicants for every job vacancy in the
employment service and manual jobs account for 65.6 percent of all
the vacancies, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
