<DOCNO> XIE19990304.0043 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French National Assembly Approves Amsterdam Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The French National Assembly
approved on Wednesday with 447 votes for and 75 against the
Amsterdam Treaty which will bring about greater political and
economic integration among European states.
</P>
<P>
Those who voted against were parliamentarians from the
Communist Party, the Greens and the Citizens' Movement party led
by Interior Minister Jean-Pierre Chevenement.
</P>
<P>
Some rightwing politicians, including former Interior Minister
Charles Pasqua who will lead a list of candidates in the European
Parliament elections in June, also voted against.
</P>
<P>
The opposers of the treaty said that France would have to
abandon a great part of its sovereignty to the European Union (EU)
if the treaty is adopted.
</P>
<P>
Under the treaty, the signing countries will hand over
decision-making powers over a series of issues from border control
to political asylum and immigration to the European Commission,
the executive body of the EU.
</P>
<P>
The French government approved the treaty at the EU Amsterdam
Summit in the summer of 1997.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the voting by the National Assembly, French
President Jacques Chirac called on the parliamentarians to support
the treaty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
