<HEADLINE> Mozambique Urges Aid to Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The government of Mozambique is in
need of 12.4 million U.S. Dollars as emergency aid to the flood
victims in central and southern parts of the country, a senior
official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Carlos do Rosario, Minister of Agriculture and Fishery made the
call on behalf of the government at a brief ceremony, attended by
diplomatic communities and business representatives in Maputo,
capital of the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to purchase food, seeds, farm tools, and
medicine and repair the destroyed infrastructure, Rosario said.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique is facing an unprecedented flood in 40 years in
southern and central parts of the country, especially in southern
Mozambique Inhambane Province, and the central Sofala Province.
</P>
<P>
It is said that 15 people have been killed by the flood, which
are destroying many of the country's infrastructure facilities,
with many roads cut off in central and southern parts of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary survey shows that about 400,000 people are affected
by the flood, with half of them in urgent need of food aid and
medical care.  
</P>
</TEXT>
