<HEADLINE> Holland Grants Tanzania $17m for Hospital Updating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 3 (Xinhua) - The Netherlands has granted
12 billion Tanzanian Shillings (about 17.39 million US Dollars) to
Tanzania for the rehabilitation of diagnostic services in 72
district and 26 regional hospitals throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
A press statement issued by the Royal Dutch embassy said
Wednesday that the project also includes the provision and
installation of essential radiological equipment including X-ray
and ultra-sound machines as well as training for radiographers
and radiologists.
</P>
<P>
"The laboratory, sterilization, operating and entail services
will be rehabilitated," it said. "Infrastructure repairs and
upgrading of basic facilities including water and electricity
supply will also be undertaken."
</P>
<P>
The total amount of the project, which officially started last
December, is approximately 20 billion Tanzanian Shillings (about
230 million U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian government contributes 40 percent of the costs
while the Netherlands provides the remaining part. 
