<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Joins in Discussions of CPPCC Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- To promote the rule of law is a
state policy set at the 15th National Congress of the ruling
Communist Party of China (CPC) and to protect the rights and
interests of women and children is an important part of the
socialist legal system.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, Member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, made the
remarks here today when taking part in panel discussions of
members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) from science and women
circles who are here to attend the current Second Session of the
Ninth CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
At the discussions, the CPPCC members put forward their
comments and proposals on a number of issues including development
of social sciences, promotion of the rule of law, amendments of
the Constitution, reform of state-owned enterprises, protection of
women's rights and interests, women's the participation in
political affairs, and development of community services.
</P>
<P>
After hearing what the CPPCC members said, Li Peng, also
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress, said the political consultation is a unique political
system in China, and he hoped that the CPPCC members would
continue to play their role of political consultation, democratic
supervision and participation in political affairs, so as to push
forward the country's economic construction and various social
undertakings onto a new stage.
</P>
<P>
The amendments of the Constitution is a major event in China
and the Party Central Committee has attached great importance to
the issue, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 15th CPC National Congress, which was held in 1997, set the
goal to develop a socialist market economy in the country and made
Deng Xiaoping Theory and Marxism, Leninism and Mao Zedong Thought
the country's guiding ideology, Li said.
</P>
<P>
"These principal issues must be reflected in the fundamental
law of the country," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Experience that has been proved successful in our
practice over the past few years should be affirmed through
legislative procedures, in order to constantly improve the
socialist legal system."
</P>
<P>
History has made it clear that China must adhere to the
strategic principle of promoting the rule of law and the will of
the Party and the people should be shown through legal procedures,
he said, noting all the political parties including the ruling CPC
should implement the principle in an all-round and serious manner.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the development of social sciences, Li said social
sciences play an important role in the reform and opening-up drive
as well as in the development of the economic and social fields. "
Social sciences should have due respect," he said.
</P>
<P>
Joining in the women CPPCC members, Li said that China has
established a complete legal system to protect the rights and
interests of women and promote gender equality with a number of
laws with the Constitution as the basic law and the Law on
Protection of Women's Rights and Interests as the main body.
</P>
<P>
To protect the rights and interests of women is one of the
symbols of civilization, he said. "Governments at all levels will
redouble their efforts to crack down on criminal activities
against women," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
