<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Meets with CPPCC Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Reform of science-technology and
educational sectors will accelerate in 1999, according to Vice-
Premier Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
National working meetings will be held on technological
innovation and educational reform late this year and their
purposes are to promote the commercialization of findings in
science and technology and quality-oriented education.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
made the remarks here today at a group discussion attended by
members of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
