<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Ethnic, Religious Affairs (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called for greater efforts today in ethnic and religious work,
saying correct handling of the ethnic and religious issues has a
direct bearing on the national unity, social stability, economic
development and strong border areas.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang made the remark this afternoon when calling on
some of the National Committee members of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), who are also
representatives from the ethnic groups and religious circle and
are here to attend the on-going Second Session of the Ninth CPPCC
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Also present on the occasion was Li Ruihuan, Standing Committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee and Chairman of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
"We should unswervingly carry out the ethnic and religious
policies, and improve our work in all fields including the ethnic
and religious field," said Jiang who is also the General Secretary
of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"This is of great significance to maintaining the solidarity
and stability of the nation, to consolidating and furthering a
relationship of equality, unity and mutual assistance among all
nationalities, and to advancing the cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics to the 21st century," he added.
</P>
<P>
Immersed in heated discussions, the CPPCC National Committee
members present at the meeting put forward opinions and
suggestions on topics such as the economic development of the
regions inhabited by ethnic groups and implementation of the
policy of freedom of religious belief.
</P>
<P>
After hearing the discussions of the CPPCC members, Jiang said
the Party and the central government have always attached great
importance to the ethnic and religious work, and have come up with
a correct way to handle the ethnic and religious issues by
implementing ethnic and religious policies with Chinese
characteristics that have the support of the Chinese people of all
nationalities.
</P>
<P>
China is a large family composed of 56 nationalities, and in
socialist China and under the leadership of the Chinese Communist
Party, all nationalities have forged a new relationship, the
ethnic regions have achieved autonomy of ethnic groups, and all
the nationalities enjoy genuine unity and equality, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
