<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Ethnic, Religious Affairs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Forging and advancing a socialist relationship among all
nationalities have always been a basic principle of our Party in
dealing with ethnic problems, and all the Chinese nationalities,
either the Han nationality or the ethnic groups live together
harmoniously and enjoy equality," the Chinese leader pointed out,
calling for the people of all nationalities to continue to hold
high the banner of nationality unity, adhere to the ethnic
policies of the Party, improve the autonomy of ethnic groups,
oppose activities of any form aimed at splitting the nationality
unity and contribute to the social stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also urged the areas inhabited by ethnic groups to speed
up their economic development and social progress to enhance the
unity of all nationalities.
</P>
<P>
"The economic and social development in the areas inhabited by
ethnic groups has a direct bearing on the modernization drive of
the whole country," he said, adding that "only when the
development in these areas is accelerated, could the whole Chinese
nation be revitalized."
</P>
<P>
"We still have a lot of work to do in order to accelerate the
development of the areas inhabited by ethnic groups," Jiang said,
pointing to the fact that the central government has already taken
and will take more special policies and measures in that regard.
</P>
<P>
On the religious issue, Jiang said: "We should first fully
carry out the religious policies of the Party, improve the
handling of religious affairs, and guide the religion to adapt
itself to the socialist society of China."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that respecting and protecting the freedom of
religious belief is a basic policy of the Party and government,
and the Party members should unite with the religious people, and
help them contribute to the country's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He explained that there are two aspects about guiding the
religion to adapt itself to the socialist society of China. First,
the religious people should abide by laws of socialist China;
secondly, the religious people should contribute as much as
possible to the unity of the motherland and the nationalities and
social progress.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the important role of the CPPCC members in this
regard, Jiang said their active participation in state affairs
vividly reflects the policies of equality among all nationalities
and freedom of religious belief in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
