<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails Opening of NPC Session (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Friday issue of the People's
Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial hailing
the opening of the Second Session of the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), the country's top legislature.
</P>
<P>
"People are the owners of our country, and the NPC session,
held once every year, is an occasion for people to exercise state
power," says the editorial, titled "People's interests rule
supreme."
</P>
<P>
Describing the upcoming NPC session as "a very important
meeting", the editorial says that the session is of great
significance for greeting the 50th founding anniversary of the
People's Republic of China on October 1 and the return of Macao at
the end of this year, as well as for further promoting the great
cause of China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
"It will also help mobilize, organize and encourage people of
all ethnic groups across the country to do a good job in various
aspects this year," it says.
</P>
<P>
The NPC session, scheduled to open in Beijing tomorrow morning,
will hear and examine a Government Work Report to be delivered by
Premier Zhu Rongji, discuss a draft amendment to the Chinese
Constitution, and deliberate some other draft laws and documents.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that 1998 was a year of great triumphs for
the Chinese people, who, under the leadership of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), withstood the strong impact of the Asian
financial crisis, won the battle against the worst flooding in
decades and maintained a steady growth of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
It goes on to say that 1999 will turn out to be a year of
particular significance in the Chinese history, as many major
events are expected to happen this year and the country will have
many difficulties to overcome.
</P>
</TEXT>
