<HEADLINE> Key Projects in Shanghai Insured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Dazhong and Ping'an insurance
companies decided today to issue property insurance in the amount
of 3.1 billion yuan for the construction of three highway bridges
across the Huangpu River and a tunnel in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The two insurance companies will insure the bridges and their
approaches, and the lighting, telecommunications, ventilation,
drainage and fire-fighting systems.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that the insurance industry is now playing a
larger role in guaranteeing urban engineering projects, said one
project official.
</P>
<P>
The Yangpu Bridge, one of the three construction projects, will
be the cable bridge with the largest cable span in the world.
Another bridge, linking Nanshi and the Pudong New Area, will be
the longest cable bridge in the world. 
