<HEADLINE> Manila Sets New Date for Autonomous Region Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
Thursday signed into law a measure allowing incumbent officials of
the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao (ARMM) to serve their
full three-year terms in a drive to accelerate development in the
south.
</P>
<P>
The law postpones the date of elections for ARMM governor, vice
governor and the regional legislative assembly, from March 8 to
the second Monday of September 1999.
</P>
<P>
He said the law will help put on the fast track the
development of Mindanao because ARMM officials will no longer be
distracted by politics from doing their jobs.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremonies of the law, Estrada praised the
congress for the speedy passage of the measure, which he said,
comes at a time when his administration is vigorously pursuing a
lasting peace agreement with Muslim rebels in the south.
</P>
<P>
"There is no doubt that a stable political environment in
Mindanao is critical for the island to attain peace and progress,"
he said. 
</P>
