<HEADLINE> Premier Urges People to Press Ahead Despite Difficulties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji today
called on the Chinese people to seize the opportunities and press
ahead despite difficulties in their reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier made the remark at a group meeting with
members of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) who are here to attend the on-going Second Session of the
CPPCC Ninth National Committee this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, CPPCC member He Zhukang said that some
problems cropped up in the process of reforms and development have
been solved and the remaining deep-rooted ones must be solved
through reforms.
</P>
<P>
