Speaking of the Chinese government's resumption of its exercise
of sovereignty over Macao on December 20 this year, Jiang said
that this will be another significant event in the history of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Macao to its motherland marks a complete ending
for the history of foreign occupation of and rule over a piece of
Chinese territory, and the resolution of the Macao issue will set
another successful example for seeking motherland reunification
according to the principle of 'one country, two systems'," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
