<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President on HK's Prosperity &AMP; Macao's Return (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today that he has full confidence in Hong Kong's long-term
prosperity and stability, as well as in a smooth return of Macao
to its motherland at the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
"'One country, two systems' is a fundamental principle which
the central government will unswervingly adhere to," Jiang, also
general-secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, told government advisors from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and Macao during a meeting this
morning.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Ninth National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), China'
s top advisory body, was also present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong and Macao members of the Ninth CPPCC National
Committee are here for the ongoing second session of the committee,
which opened Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that over the past 20 months since Hong Kong's
return to its motherland and the founding of the Hong Kong SAR,
the principles of "one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" and a high degree of autonomy for Hong Kong
have been fully implemented in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Today's Hong Kong has witnessed no changes to its original
social and economic systems or way of life, and the legal system
there has remained basically unchanged," said Jiang. "Facts have
proved that the principle of 'one country, two systems' is both
pragmatic and feasible, and has great vitality."
</P>
<P>
"In both interior areas and Hong Kong, we must conscientiously
safeguard this principle when we do anything or handle any
problems, and must not do any harm to it," he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
