<DOCNO> XIE19990304.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Pirate Gang Uncovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police have cracked a
murder case masterminded by international pirates.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 20 people have been arrested on charges of killing 23
Chinese seamen, said a spokesman for the Guangdong Provincial
Public Security Department at a press briefing held here today in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Police also seized seven guns, two iron-clad ships and other
booty.
</P>
<P>
A cargo ship belonging to a Hong Kong shipping company left the
port of Shanghai on November 12 last year after being loaded with
14,000 tons of slag at the Baoshan Iron and Steel Complex. The
ship was manned by 23 Chinese sailors. No information was received
on the ship's whereabouts after it reported its location at sea
near Dongshan Island in east China's Fujian Province on November
16.
</P>
<P>
Seven bodies bound up and weighted with iron ingots were
spotted on the surface of the sea near the city of Shanwei and
Lufeng and Huilai counties between December 2 and 22. A few days
later, three more bodies were seen in the region. Preliminary
investigations revealed they were the bodies of Chinese seamen who
had been aboard the cargo ship.
</P>
<P>
A suspect was detained on January 3, and he confessed and
related the entire story to authorities including the whereabouts
of the two chief criminals, one an Indonesian. Police later
arrested more suspects in Guangdong, Fujian, Sichuan, Liaoning and
Shaanxi provinces and in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
An investigation showed the murders belonged to an
international gang of pirates whose ringleaders were from
Southeast Asia. They recruited more than a dozen criminals in
Henan and Sichuan provinces and provinces in northeast China, and
purchased guns and ships.
</P>
<P>
On November 16, they robbed the cargo ship, killed all 23
Chinese seamen on aboard and threw their bodies into the sea. On
November 26, the pirates handed the ship over to a dozen foreign
seamen who then sailed it out into the high sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
