<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR Government Opens Beijing Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) officially announced the
establishment of its Beijing Office today.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, vice premier of the State Council, extended
congratulations on behalf of the State Council at the reception to
celebrate the opening.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the SAR Government's Beijing Office will help bring
closer ties between the SAR government and the central government,
as well as government in all provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities in inland areas.
</P>
<P>
It will also play an important role in increasing exchanges
between inland areas and Hong Kong and their mutual understanding,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed thanks to all those who made contributions to
the process of Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The Office, headed by Bowen Leung, will serve as a bridge
linking the Hong Kong SAR and inland areas, and provide accurate
and current information about the SAR to the central government
and the governments of all provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The office consists of three sections: the Economic Affairs,
Trade and Liaison Section, the Immigration Section, and the
Information and Office Administration Section, according to Leung.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong SAR, said the
future of Hong Kong is closely intertwined with the future of the
country, and he believes that the Beijing Office will be a very
important part of enhancing liaison with the motherland.
</P>
