<HEADLINE> Tiny Baby Girl Survives in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A newborn baby girl weighing only
755 grams has survived for a week, the longest time ever for an
infant of this size.
</P>
<P>
The tiny infant was born on February 26 at the Shanghai No. 1
People's Hospital after a pregnancy of 33 weeks. The 30-year-old
mother, Liu, became pregnant six times since she married eight
years ago, but all previous pregnancies ended in miscarriages.
</P>
<P>
Hong Jianguo, a local pediatrician, said, "Seldom has medical
history recorded a case of a newborn weighing under 1,000 grams
surviving. Survival of low-weight newborns after preventing
miscarriage is even rarer."
</P>
<P>
The girl is living in an incubator and nurses are monitoring
her around-the-clock, and her parents can look at her through a
window every day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
