<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Jolts Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake, measuring 6.1
on the Richter scale, Thursday jolted Zamboanga City, the southern
Philippines, but no damage was reported, the Philippine Institute
of Volcanology and Seismology said.
</P>
<P>
In a preliminary report, the institute said the epicenter of
the earthquake, which occurred at 4:52 p.m. local time (08:52
GMT), was under the Celebes Sea, 113 kilometers south of Zamboanga
city, Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was felt in a few nearby cities and aftershocks were
likely, the institute said. 
