<HEADLINE> Manila Rules Out Military Solution on Muslim Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
said Thursday that his administration is not resorting to a
military solution in dealing with the Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF).
</P>
<P>
Estrada said that despite the postponement of his meeting with
MILF chairman Hashim Salamat, his administration is pursuing
efforts to keep the peace process on track.
</P>
<P>
"We are exhausting all remedies to see the peace process will
be a success. So I am not using the military solution to solve
this problem with the MILF," he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, some politicians, including former President Fidel V.
Ramos, advised Estrada to refrain from resorting to a military
solution in dealing with the MILF, government officials said.
</P>
<P>
But Estrada said Ramos did not need to give him that advice
since he is resolved to ensure the success of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Estrada has repeatedly said Mindanao, the southern Philippines,
 cannot realize its full economic potential unless genuine and
lasting peace reigns in the island. 
</P>
