<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Closing More Mountain Areas For Afforestation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China plans to close off 48
million ha of mountain areas for afforestation in the next 12
years, according to the National Forestry Administration.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 2010 the country will have added 33 million ha
of forests. This method has been used traditionally in China
because of the low cost and quick yield. It is used especially in
remote areas of severe water and soil erosion, according to an
administration official.
</P>
<P>
China has already put more than 30 million ha of mountain areas
under restrictions, but the official admitted that, because of a
lack of awareness and investment by local governments, some closed
off areas have not been protected well and there are still 48
million ha of mountain areas that need to be closed.
</P>
<P>
To make certain the plan takes effect, the NAF will designate 3.
2 million ha of mountain areas as key areas, where forests, bushes,
and wasteland will be closed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
