<HEADLINE> Information Infrastructure Expo Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Over 100 international and local
companies are demonstrating to the public the actual applications
of the latest electronic and information technology (IT) in
business and people's daily life at an IT infrastructure
exposition opened here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Information Infrastructure Expo &AMP; Conference 1999,
is organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council and co-
organized by the Information Technology &AMP; broadcasting Bureau (
ITBB) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR). The
event will run from March 4 to 7 at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The event aims at promoting Hong Kong as the region's premier
IT and telecommunication hub and emphasizes the importance of
building Hong Kong's information infrastructure in the digital
century to retain Hong Kong's competitive edge and to drive its
overall economic expansion.
</P>
<P>
The expo houses seven thematic pavilions, showcasing a wide
range of advanced IT and telecommunications services and products.
</P>
<P>
These pavilions include Government On Line (Electronic Service
Delivery), Information Gallery, Telecom City, E-Commerce
Marketplace, Cybermedia Zone, Global IT Community and Technology
Village.
</P>
<P>
One of the highlights at the Expo is the Government On Line
Pavilion at which ITBB presents the government's project on
Electronic Service Delivery for the first time in a home setting
environment with mock-up features to show how this implementation
impacts the general public in communications with the government
in the future.
</P>
<P>
Five government departments including Hongkong Post, Inland
Revenue Department, Information Services Department, Office of the
Telecommunications Authority and Information Technology Service
Department, together with the Hong Kong Tourist Association
introduce their additional services available through the use of
IT.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Article Numbering Association, Hong Kong
Institute of Engineers and Hong Kong University of Science and
Technology demonstrate various IT applications on supply chain
management, education, transportation, healthcare and other
locally-developed technologies.
</P>
<P>
Besides, leading multinational and local companies joining the
Expo include: Nortel, Cisco, Hewlett-Packard, AT&AMP;T, 3COM, Dell,
Acer, Chinese Books Cyberstore, Linkage, Yahoo, IBM, Reuters, Hong
Kong Telecom, China Motion, SmarTone, China InfoBank, City Telecom,
Netvigator, and Hong Kong Economic Times.
</P>
<P>
The best and latest IT offerings by companies and organizations
from Australia, Canada, China's mainland and the United States are
displayed at the expo for the first time.
</P>
<P>
There is an "Open Forum" theater inside the Expo where
exhibitors conduct product talks or demonstrations, which are
broadcast live on Internet real-time via the event's website.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the expo also features innovative IT technologies
presented by the winners of the Hong Kong IT Excellence Awards
organized by the Hong Kong Computer Society.
</P>
<P>
There is a Cyber-Cafe and an IT Quiz and Game Center where
visitors can participate in interesting on-line quizzes and games
with chances to win prizes.
</P>
<P>
To coincide with the expo, a high-level conference is held on
Thursday with 34 world-renowned speakers exchanging their views on
concerned issues in the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
