<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Italy Hold Mixed Committee on Economy and Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Italian Economic and
Trade Mixed Committee held its fifth meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
Minister Shi Guangsheng of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation and visiting Italian Foreign Trade Minister Piero
Fassino co-hosted the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Shi explained that the economies of China and Italy are
strongly complementary and have massive potential for further
development.
</P>
<P>
He urged the two governments to continue supporting their
businesses in economic and trade cooperation, and said China
welcomes investment from Italy.
</P>
<P>
He hoped Italian businesses would transfer technology to China
by setting up joint-ventures and bring bilateral trade relations
to a new stage together.
</P>
<P>
The Italian side suggested establishing a work group on
intellectual property rights under the mixed committee. Shi agreed
with the idea, saying he hopes the two sides enhance cooperation
in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shi put forward the idea of setting up a bilateral
discussion mechanism at divisional and bureau level by meeting
annually in Beijing and Rome alternately.
</P>
<P>
Shi also expressed the hope that Italy will play a positive
role in the European Union's trade policy towards China.
</P>
<P>
Fassino said he highly appreciated China's role in the Asian
financial crisis, especially the commitment not to devalue the
Renminbi and maintaining economic reforms in a tough environment.
</P>
<P>
He said Italy was in favor of China's entry into the World
Trade Organization, and hoped that goal could be realized this
year.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Shi met with representatives of Italian
businessmen in China and listened to their ideas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
