questioned by the police for eight hours about suspicions that he
may have peddled favors to retired general Avigdor Ben-Gal in
exchange for favorable testimony in a libel suit.
</P>
<P>
During the questioning, Sharon denied that he had offered
bribes to Ben-Gal for his testimony against the local daily
Haaretz.
</P>
<P>
