<DOCNO> XIE19990304.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Has Over 10 Million Medium and Small Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China now has over 10 million
medium and small industrial and commercial enterprises, making up
90 percent of the total registered enterprises, according to the
State Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value of the medium and small enterprises
account for 60 percent of the country's total, and the pre-tax
profits for about 40 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises are also important to the country's economy
in that they are providing about 75 percent of the urban jobs.
</P>
<P>
They also account for about 60 percent of the country's annual
export value of 150 billion US dollars in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
