<DOCNO> XIE19990304.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Biggest Cypress Attracting Visitors to Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A 2,500-year-old big cypress in
Nyingchi Prefecture in east Tibet, has become one of the most
famous scenic spots in the region.
</P>
<P>
The cypress, is 50 meters high and 5.8 meters in diameter, and
is the biggest of its kind in China. Local people built a one-
meter-high wall around the cypress to protect the "Sacred Tree".
</P>
<P>
The tree is growing in a cypress woods, about four kilometers
away from the Bayi (August 1) Town, where the Nyingchi Prefecture
Government is located. The tree is attracting people young and old
both in and outside the region to "pay homage".
</P>
<P>
"I wish the tree would bring good luck to my business this year,
" said Xia Yi, a merchant from Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
A middle-aged Tibetan woman, authorized as a "Tree Guard",
stood beside the cypress and collected five yuan as protection fee
for the tree from every group of visitors.
</P>
<P>
The big cypress and other trees in the woods, which are listed
under the second category of state protection, often receive "
medical checks" from experts and would be carefully treated if any
disease and insect pests infected them.
</P>
<P>
Nyingchi is located on the lower reaches of the Yarlung Zangbo
River, with a lower sea level than other local areas and a mild
and moist climate, which allow more kinds of trees to grow.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
