<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Japanese-US Security Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that Japan will honor
its commitment and keep on pursuing peace and development, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today at a weekly
press conference.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on the new Japan-U.S. defense guidelines,
Zhu said that China has maintained a clear and consistent stance
on the security cooperation between Japan and the United States.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Japanese-US defense cooperation is a bilateral
arrangement made against the special historical background and it
should be strictly confined to the Japan-U.S. bilateral ties, or
it will disturb the Asian neighboring countries and complicate the
regional security situation.
</P>
<P>
China has noticed that Japan and the United States have made
clear in the new guidelines that Japan should conduct its military
action according to the Japanese constitution and for defense
purpose only, and Japan and the United States should observe the
fundamental norms of international laws and guideline of the UN
Charter in all of their activities, Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
