<HEADLINE> Cholera Deaths on Increase in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has recorded 870 cases of
cholera with 100 people having died since the outbreak of the
disease in early January, according to Health and Child Welfare
Minister Timothy Stamps.
</P>
<P>
Updating parliament Wednesday on the current situation, Stamps
said cholera outbreak had been reported in all Zimbabwe's
neighboring countries except Botswana and South Africa during the
last six months.
</P>
<P>
The situation, he said, was under control in some of the
affected areas.
</P>
<P>
" Besides the normal treatment activities in hospitals and
clinics, we have set up mobile and static treatment camps whose
main functions are to educate the public and to provide
treatment," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We admit we were initially slow in disseminating information
particularly in clinics. Staff morale was and still is slow
because there was no financial allowance for health workers in
cholera areas although we have repeatedly approached the labor
ministry," he added.
</P>
<P>
He suggested the convening of a caucus next Wednesday to
discuss some of

the issues which are too sensitive to be discussed in parliament.
</P>
</TEXT>
