<HEADLINE> 4 S. Korean Nationals Die by Consuming Alcoholic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- At least four South Korean
nationals, crewmen of MV "Am Nok Gong", died by consuming
alcoholic drinks and 12 others are in serious condition following
a party on board their ship, Antara News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The voyage was from the Surabaya port of Tanjung Perak in East
Java to the port of Tanjung Intan in Cilacap, a town in southern
Central Java.
</P>
<P>
Cilacap police chief Lt. Col. F.R. Andi Lolo confirmed the
incident and said that a report on the incident was received from
PT Gesury Lloyd, the shipping agency for the South Korean vessel.
</P>
<P>
"PT Gesuri Lloyd reported to the local police station that some
crewmen were dead on the ship after they consumed much alcoholic
drink while on their way from Surabaya to Cilacap," Lolo was
quoted by Antara News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Following the report, police sent a rescue team and some of its
detectives to the ship, which moored at the Tanjung Intan port on
Wednesday morning, to investigate the cause of the incident, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Police were still investigating the ship and questioning some
crewmen on board, Antara said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
