<HEADLINE> 9 Tamil Rebels Killed in Fighting in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
killed nine Tamil rebels Tuesday and Wednesday during
confrontations in the north and east of the country, a military
spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops killed three rebels
Wednesday in Tanduvan in the northern Wanni area.
</P>
<P>
Also on Wednesday, government troops destroyed a bunker manned
by four Tamil rebels at Paranthan in the northern Jaffna
peninsula, said the spokesman, adding that the rebels were all
killed during the attack.
</P>
<P>
Dewage said government troops conducted a cordon-and-search
operation and confronted a group of rebels at Akkaraipattu in the
eastern Ampara area, killing two rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state of its own in the north
and east of the country. 
</P>
