<HEADLINE> 862 Firms to Participate in UAE Defense Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A total of 862 firms from 43
countries have confirmed participation in the 4th International
Defense Exhibition to be held in Abu Dhabi on March 14-18.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, in terms of space, the Index '99 was 33 percent over
booked" despite the global economic slowdown and mergers between
big companies which affected exhibitions, Al Suwaidi, chairman of
the Military Committee for International Defense Exhibitions and
Conferences said.
</P>
<P>
Among the 862 firms, "765 were individual entities and the rest
subsidiaries or affiliates," Al Suwaidi said to the press Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The participants include some of the world's biggest defense
manufacturers, such as British Aerospace, Marconi Electronic
Systems, GIAT, Dassault Aviation, Thomson CSF, Siemens, Lockheed
Martin, and Ratheon Industries.
</P>
<P>
In the forefront of participating countries are the U.S.,
Britain, France, Germany, Italy, and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
According to Al Suwaidi, major deals will be announced during
the show.
</P>
<P>
"The UAE will not interfere with any country wishing to
announce deals here or anywhere. Index is a stage for such
announcements," he said.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the importance of the Idex '99 for the Gulf, the
chairman said: "for the GCC (Gulf Cooperation Council) and Arab
countries, it is an event that can not be missed and they look to
it as an excellent venue to see the latest technology in defense
equipment."
</P>
<P>
As a special event held every two years with government
support, the defense show has put the UAE on the top of the world
exhibition map.
</P>
<P>
A total of 725 defense manufacturers participated in the 1997
exhibition, which attracted around 25,000 visitors, including 65
official delegations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
