<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Spokesman on NPC Session Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Second Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) is an important event in the
political life of the Chinese people as it will discuss and decide
on many issues that are important for the general public,
according to an NPC spokesman.
</P>
<P>
 Briefing reporters on the session's agenda at the first news
conference held by the NPC Second Session prior to its opening
tomorrow, Spokesman Zeng Jianhui said the government work report
to be heard and examined by NPC deputies will list a series of
reform and opening-up measures.
</P>
<P>
The session will deliberate and vote on a draft contract law,
he said. It will be one of the fundamental laws having a close
relevance on the establishment and development of a socialist
market economy in China, he said. "When enacted, the law will play
a major role not only in people's daily life, but also in
safeguarding a healthy growth of the country's market economy,"
Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
The session will examine a draft method for the election of
deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress from the Macao
Special Administrative Region to be established later this year,
he said. This is of great significance for Macao's return to the
motherland and the implementation of the "one country, two systems
" policy in the future Macao SAR, he said.
</P>
<P>
The session will also examine a draft amendment to the
Constitution, whose passage will provide a constitutional
guarantee for China's further reform, opening-up and modernization
drive, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The NPC session will hold six news conferences covering the
subjects of foreign affairs, state-owned enterprise reform,
foreign trade, financial work and legislation, Zeng said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
