<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Farmers Find Rare Turtle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A rare turtle was recently found
by farmers digging in the sand in Weishan Yi Autonomous County in
southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Trionyx Steindachneri, from the turtle family, weighs 8.75
kg and is 71 cm long. Experts estimate that it is several hundreds
years old.
</P>
<P>
This kind of turtle is mainly found in Viet Nam and Myanmar and
is under state-level protection in China.
</P>
<P>
The turtle was confiscated by forestry department officials who
discovered the farmers trying to sell it. It has now been sent to
the local nature reserve protection center.
</P>
<P>
Yang Datong, a researcher at the Kunming Animal Research
Institute, believes that this kind of turtle, rarely found in the
western parts of the province, is worth studying if more can be
located in the area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
