<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay Beats Guatemala in Copa de la Paz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay fought back from behind
to score a 3-2 victory over Guatemala in Guatemala City on
Wednesday in the first Copa de la Paz tournament.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala dominated most of the game, but couldn't prevent
Paraguay from tying and taking the lead in the last five minutes
of the game.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala opened the scoring in the 19th minute when Cesar
Alegria converted on a pass from Jorge Rodas.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay tied it in the 70th minute when Juan Peralta, who had
just entered the game, scored on a pass from Tomas Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala retook the lead in the 76th minute on a goal by
Everaldo Valencia.
</P>
<P>
But Paraguay's Juan Carlos Centurion tied it again in the 86th
minute after German Ruana was expelled for aggression. Minutes
later, Mauro Caballero scored the winning goal, converting a long-
distance pass.
</P>
<P>
In the first game, a surprisingly strong Jamaican team held
tournament favorite Bolivia to a scoreless draw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
