<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourism Sector Enjoys Funding Bonanza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Today's overseas edition of People'
s Daily reported that China's rapidly growing tourism sector has
been a focal point of investment over the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The sector has attracted total investments of over 370 billion
yuan (44.58 billion US dollars) since the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
The hotel industry pioneered the nation's effort to attract
foreign investment. The sector used foreign direct investment (FDI)
totaling five billion US dollars between the late 1970s through
the late 1980s to build a number of tourist hotels in major cities
and economically developed areas.
</P>
<P>
Foreign funds have since been used to develop resorts, tourist
products, scenic sites and modern entertainment venues.
</P>
<P>
The hotel industry has attracted foreign investment totaling 15
billion US dollars, with an additional two billion dollars
earmarked for the development of resorts, one billion dollars for
scenic sites and two billion dollars for villa and apartment
complexes.
</P>
<P>
The 734 foreign-funded hotels currently have over 178,000 rooms.
</P>
<P>
The focus of foreign investment has shifted from highly
developed coastal areas to inland regions with abundant tourism
resources and from new projects to upgrading older facilities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
