<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction Begins on New Hydro-electric Power Station For Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Work has started on another large
hydro-electric power station on the upper reaches of the Yellow
river, China's second longest river.
</P>
<P>
The Gongboxia Hydroelectirc Station is being built at the
junction of Xunhua and Hualong counties in northwestern Qinghai
Province. The five generation units will have a total combined
capacity of 1.5 million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13 big and medium-sized hydro-electric power
stations are expected total be built on the upper reaches of the
Yellow River. This is the fourth after the Longyangxia, Lijiaxia,
and Liujiaxia hyrdoelectric power stations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
