<HEADLINE> Beijing Set to Host International Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Beijing International
Fair will be held in the International Exhibition Center here
between May 20 and 24.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature new technology and products related to
environmental and resource protection. A special exhibition area
will be available for the display of unpolluted farm produce known
as "green food".
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to attract representatives from a long
list of countries and regions, including Belorussia, Bulgaria,
Egypt, Turkey, Romania, the Republic of Korea, Canada, Japan,
Columbia, Mongolia, Laos, Ukraine, Lithuania, Iran, Czechoslovakia,
Viet Nam, Hungary and Poland.
</P>
<P>
The large-scale biennial fair is sponsored by the China Council
for the Promotion of International Trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
