<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Thoroughfare Set for Facelift </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chang'an Avenue, the main
thoroughfare in the Chinese capital, is slated for a major
facelift.
</P>
<P>
The project is scheduled for completion by October 1 (National
Day) to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The major renovation project will encompass structures between
the Dongdan and Xidan intersections. Walkways will take on a new
look and the east section of the avenue from Dongdan to Jianguomen
will be widened from 35 meters to 50 meters.
</P>
<P>
Some 10.8 ha will be landscaped, and the existing 43.84 ha of
plants and trees will be rearranged. Fountains and sculptures will
be added to lawns in Qianmen and Jianguomen intersections.
</P>
<P>
Experts in charge of the renovation project have also announced
special requirements for signs and exterior lights on buildings
lining the avenue.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
