<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Concludes Visit to Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian left here for China on Wednesday after he wrapped up his
official good-will visit to Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Those who went to see him off at the airport were Mexican
Defense Minister Enrique Cervantes and Chinese Ambassador to
Mexico Shen Yunao.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Chi, who is also vice chairman of China's
Central Military Commission and a State Councilor, met with
President Ernesto Zedillo, Defense Minister Cervantes and Navy
Minister Ramon Lorenzo.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged views on developing military ties and
other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Chi is the first Chinese defense minister to visit Mexico at
the invitation of his Mexican counterpart. 
</P>
</TEXT>
