<HEADLINE> Vietnam Wants to Host World Taekwondo Cup 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 4 (xinhua) -- Vietnam expects to host world
taekwondo cup 2000, Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's National Sports and Physical Training Committee has
decided to provide 5,000 U.S. dollars to Vietnam's National
Taekwondo Federation in an effort to obtain the right to host the
world taekwondo cup 2000.
</P>
<P>
The event is expected to kick off in late 2000, following the
taekwondo event of the Sydney olympics.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese athletes will take part in the qualifying rounds for
Sydney olympics in Croatia in July and in the Philippines in
October this year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese athletes will also compete in two annual
international events, one sponsored by Samsung in Vietnam's Ho Chi
Minh city, and the other for youth in Hanoi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
