<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meeting of NPC Session Held in Beijing -1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The preparatory meeting of the
Second Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), was
held in Beijing this morning.
</P>
<P>
Those attending the preparatory meeting elected a 169-member
presidium and the secretary-general of the session through an
electronic voting system, and passed the agenda of the session,
which is to open here tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, Chairman of the Ninth NPC Standing Committee, presided
over the meeting attended by 2,699 deputies.
</P>
<P>
He said that the guiding ideology of the session is:
</P>
<P>
-- Hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and take
the basic line of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) and the
guidelines of the 15th National Congress of the CPC as the
guidance;
</P>
<P>
-- Continue to push forward the reforms and opening up, and
maintain a sustainable, fast and healthy development of the
national economy;
</P>
<P>
-- Further handle well the relations between reforms,
development and stability, and ensure social and political
stability;
</P>
<P>
-- Actively promote the process of building China into a
socialist country ruled by law;
</P>
<P>
-- Unify people's thinking, strengthen their resolve, seize the
opportunity, press ahead despite difficulties, unite as one and
work hard to promote the all-round development of various
undertakings and the all-round progress of the society; and
</P>
<P>
-- Greet the 50 anniversary of the founding of New China and
the smooth return of Macao with new successes scored under the
leadership of the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
