<DOCNO> XIE19990304.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meeting of NPC Session Held in Beijing -2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Presidium is composed of over 20 Party and state leaders,
including Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central
Committee and state president; Li Peng, chairman of the NPC
Standing Committee; Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee; Hu Jintao, state vice-president; and Wei Jianxing.
member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the
CPC Central Committee and secretary of the Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection.
</P>
<P>
According to conventional practice, beginning from the second
session of each term of the NPC, the members of the State Council
and president of the Supreme People's Court and procurator-general
of the Supreme People's Procuratorate will not be included in the
presidium. Hence, Premier Zhu Rongji and Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
are not members of the presidium of this session.
</P>
<P>
Other members of the presidium included are leaders of non-
Communist parties and the All-China Federation of Industry and
Commerce, patriotic personages without party affiliations, leading
members of the central Party, government and military bodies,
armed police units, and the people's organizations, deputies from
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) and Macao,
deputies from national pillar industries and from science and
technology, social sciences, education, literature and art, sports,
public health and religious circles.
</P>
<P>
The presidium members also include deputies representing
overseas Chinese, workers, farmers, soldiers of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) and armed policemen, deputies from ethnic
minorities with comparatively large population, heads of
delegations to the NPC session from all provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities directly under the central government,
and heads of the PLA delegation and the Hong Kong SAR delegation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
