</P>
<P>
-- Hearing, deliberating and approving a report on the
implementation of the 1998 national economic and social
development plan and a draft plan for 1999 national economic and
social development;
</P>
<P>
-- Hearing, examining and approving a report on the
implementation of the 1998 central and local budgets and the draft
budgets for 1999;
</P>
<P>
-- Examining NPC Standing Committee's draft amendment to the
Constitution of the People's Republic of China;
</P>
<P>
-- Examining a draft contract law;
</P>
<P>
-- Examining a draft method for the election of deputies to the
Ninth National People's Congress from the Macao Special
Administrative Region;
</P>
<P>
-- Hearing and examining work reports by the NPC Standing
Committee, the Supreme People's Court and the Supreme People's
Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
 The Second Session of the Ninth NPC is to last 11 days (March
5-15), the shortest for such sessions over the past two decades
since the start of reforms and opening up in 1978, according to
the preparatory meeting. 
</P>
