<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Presidium of NPC Session Holds First Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The just-elected presidium of the
Second Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC),
China's legislature, held its first meeting here this morning.
</P>
<P>
The presidium first elected its executive chairmen. Elected as
such were NPC Standing Committee Chairman Li Peng, 19 NPC Standing
Committee vice-chairmen including Tian Jiyun, Xie Fei and Jiang
Chunyun, and Secretary-General of the NPC Standing Committee He
Chunlin.
</P>
<P>
The meeting approved an agenda for the upcoming NPC annual
session, which is scheduled to open tomorrow morning, adopted
group assignments for the session's executive chairmen and decided
that He Chunlin, Wang Zhongyu, Wang Weicheng, Zeng Jianhui and Hu
Guangbao serve as deputy secretaries-general of the session.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also adopted a method for bill approval procedures
for the Second Session of the Ninth NPC, which stipulates that an
electronic voting system be used, that approval require favorable
votes by more than half of all the deputies, and that for voting
on a draft amendment to the Constitution, voting by secret ballot
be used and approval require a two-thirds majority in favor.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the meeting decided that the deadline for bill
submission will be 6 p.m. on March 10. According to law, one
delegation of deputies or more than 30 deputies can jointly submit
a bill to the session within the scope of the NPC's functions and
powers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
