<HEADLINE> Cardoso Predicts Real's Exchange Rate to Normalize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Cardoso said Wednesday that the exchange rate between the real and
the U.S. dollar will normalize in the second quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The president made this statement when the exchange rate
reached 2.23 reals to the dollar on Tuesday, a situation he
considers to be exaggerated.
</P>
<P>
When the decision was made in mid-January to let the local
currency float freely in Brazil, the exchange rate was 1.21 reals
to one dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank said the dollar is currently being sold at 2.
20 reals within the country.
</P>
<P>
The bank said Brazil's international reserves fell to 35
billion dollars on Wednesday compared with 35.33 billion dollars
on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
