falls on October 1. Shanghai will be the first Chinese city with
two large-scaled international airports.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's air traffic has grown by an average annual rate of
23 percent in recent years, with the passenger volume hitting 13.7
million in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Sources note that Hongqiao Airport's annual handling capacity
of 9.6 million passengers has failed to keep pace with rapidly
increasing demand. 
