<HEADLINE> Hewitt Beats Rafter Again in ATP Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Qualifier Lleyton Hewitt beat
fellow Australian Pat Rafter in the second round of the Scottsdale
ATP tournament in straight sets here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It was less than two months ago that the Adelaide teenager, who
turned 18 just last week, upset his double Grand Slam champion
compatriot in Sydney. His 7-6 (7-5), 6-1 triumph was identical to
the one he notched last January.
</P>
<P>
There was triumph for France as sixth seed Cedric Pioline took
an easy 6-1, 6-2 win into the quarter-finals over Aussie Andrew
Ilie.
</P>
<P>
Jerome Golmard advanced when Ecuadoran opponent Nicolas
Lapentti sprained his right ankle and retired while leading the
first set 5-3.
</P>
<P>
The South American was scheduled to have an x-ray before
deciding on whether to compete at the Super Nine event in Indian
Wells, which starts on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Title holder American Andre Agassi, seeded third behind
American Pete Sampras and Rafter, was scheduled to play Wednesday
night against Mariano Zapaleta of Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
