<HEADLINE> Industrial Safety Awareness Highlighted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A recent spate of industrial
accidents is urging the State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC)
to take measures to enhance employee's safety awareness at work,
today's China Daily said.
</P>
<P>
The commission designated May 9-15 as "safe production
publicity week". Various measures will be adopted during the week
to spread knowledge of safety at work, said Shan Chunchang,
director of SETC's Work Safety Management Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Activities include awareness campaigns in the media, public
quizzes and speeches.
</P>
<P>
Special fund will be allocated to ensure the week's campaign
brings about good results, according to SETC sources.
</P>
<P>
As rural workers make up the majority of workplace accident
victims, and in many cases are held responsible for the accidents,
it is vital to provide them with safety education, Shan said.
</P>
<P>
Coinciding with the week-long publicity campaign, nationwide
accident-prevention inspections will be conducted to plug safety
loopholes and rectify loose management and discipline, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
