of selected goods of the European Union (EU) to post bonds to
cover 100 percent duties that may be imposed due to a trade
dispute with Europe over bananas.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Trade Representative Office said the U.S. customs
service beginning Wednesday would require importers of EU goods
ranging from Scottish cashmere sweaters to Italian cheese to post
bonds to cover the threatened duties. (US-EU-Banana)
</P>
<P>
