WASHINGTON -- Two people were killed and over 30 others injured
when a bus carrying elementary school students home from a ski
outing crashed and overturned on a narrow canyon road in New
Mexico State of the United States, said reports reaching here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
One child and one adult died Tuesday after being thrown through
the windshield just outside Santa Fe in the state, the reports
said. (US-Bus-Accident)
</P>
<P>
