<HEADLINE> Sonics Olden Polynice Fined $5,000 for Obscene Gesture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Seattle SuperSonics center
Olden Polynice was fined $5,000 today by the NBA for making an
obscene gesture toward the fans after Monday's game at Sacramento.
</P>
<P>
Polynice offered his gesture at the Arco Arena crowd following
Seattle's 105-102 victory. Polynice and Billy Owens were making
their return to Sacramento after leaving the Kings as free agents
prior to the season.
</P>
<P>
Both players were booed repeatedly by the crowd, but while
Owens flourish, Polynice managed just three points on 1-of-5
shooting.
</P>
<P>
It is the fourth set of fines this season handed out by NBA
vice president of operations Rod Thorn.
</P>
<P>
The first set came down on Charles Barkley of the Houston
Rockets, Steve Smith of the Atlanta Hwaks and Kendall Gill of the
New Jersey Nets.
</P>
<P>
The Portland Trail Blazers' Isaiah Rider and Chicago Bulls
coach Tim Floyd was victimized on the second round of fines and
Penny Hardaway of the Orlando Magic was the latest casualy before
Polynice. 
</P>
