<HEADLINE> Stocks End Mixed On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stock indexes ended
mixed Wednesday with the Dow Jones industrial average falling but
the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow finished down 21.73 to 9,275.88. In the session of
trading, the blue chip index gained 40 points before retreating.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite was up 6.17 at 2,265.20 and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 2.20 at 1,227.70.
</P>
<P>
The market was affected by Federal Reserve Chairman Alan
Greenspan's remarks and unexpected lower earnings for the 3Com
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Greenspan told a Congressional subcommittee in Washington that
the proposal by U.S. President Bill Clinton to invest a portion of
the Social Security Trust Fund in the stock market could harm the
U.S. economy. The remarks ruffled the market that was undergoing a
correction.
</P>
<P>
The market was also in a negative reaction in the second day to
the announcement by 3Com that its sales and earnings would fall
short of expectation. On Tuesday, the company, which sells data,
voice and video systems for the Internet and intranets, lowered
its sales at 1.41 billion U.S. dollars for the three months ended
in February from 1.5 billion dollars expected earlier.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 0.39 at 582.55 and the American Stock
Exchange index dropped 4.76 to 694.45. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies also fell 2.48 to 391.95.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume totaled 745.22 million share vs. 744.08 million in
the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
