(UNICEF) and the World Food Program, together with the U.N.
Emergency Relief Coordinator, issued in Geneva a joint statement
responding to what they describe as inaccurate and unbalanced
criticisms by Medecins sans Frontieres-France (Doctors Without
Borders) of the U.N. humanitarian program known as Operation
Lifeline Sudan and its efforts to provide assistance to the people
