<HEADLINE> Hundred Billion Dollars of Africa's Money Locked up Outside </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The figure represents one-third of Africa's 350 billion-Dollar
annual gross domestic product, Ken Kwaku, Director of the
Multilateral Investment Guarantee Agency (MIGA) of the World
Bank, said this, when he presented a paper on "Private Sector
Development through the Promotion of Direct Foreign Investment",
as part of activities to mark Investment Day at the on-going
second ECOWAS Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
Kwaku noted that the situation is precarious, saying, "there is
capital shortage in Africa and, particularly, this sub-region,"
according to a special story reaching here Wednesday night from
the Ghana News Agency.
